body:
jApiRecorder
============
A dynamic proxy to record and playback API method calls e.g. for testing porposes.

# Features
* record and/or playback an API mathod call return value.
* replace attibute values of return values via dot notation attribute path on playback.
* manipulate replacement values before setting them to the attribute values on the recorded value.

# Description
The jApiRecorder one can creat a dynamic proxy of a class to record/playback API method calls.

## Modes
There are four modes to go:
* FOREWARD - calls the original method directly and returns the value.
* RECORD - calls the original method and records the returned value.
* PB_ONLINE - tries first to get a return value from the recorded data. if there is one it will be returned,
else it calls the original method, records the return value and returns it.
* PB_OFFLINE - tries to get a return value from the recorded data. if there is none it will return null.

## ReadWriteStrategy and ContentTypeStrategy
It is possible to implement your own `ReadWriteStrategy` and/or `ContentTypeStrategy`.
You only have to implement the given interfaces.

Already implemented `ContentTypeStrategy` is:
`XStreamContentTypeStrategy` which serialize/deserialize the objects to be recorded/playbacked with XStream (XML).

Already implemented `ReadWriteStrategy` is:
`H2ReadWriteStrategy` which reads/writes the serialized objects to be recorded/playbacked within a H2 database (memory or file database).

## Attribute Replacement
One can replace attribute values in the recorded values.
Specify an attribute path from the recorded  result object in dot notation form (see [jDotNotation](http://uscexp.github.io/jDotNotation/)) to the attribute one want to change. Set a fix value or use an argument passed to the method call.
The value one want to set to an attribute in the result can be manipulated before setting it to the attribute.
E.g. one want to change a `Date` attribute of the result and change it to the current date. One can add serveral replacement value treatments to change the value, in this example to change it to the current date.

# Example
An example from a junit test (see more junit tests form more code examples):
```java
ContentTypeStrategy contentTypeStrategy = new XStreamContentTypeStrategy();
ReadWriteStrategy readWriteStrategy = new H2ReadWriteStrategy();
RecordPlaybackConfiguration recordPlaybackConfiguration = new RecordPlaybackConfiguration();
recordPlaybackConfiguration.addArgumentIndices4PrimaryKey("simpleLevel2Method", 0, 1);
TestClass testClass = (TestClass) RecordPlaybackManager.newInstance(TestClass.class, RecordPlaybackMode.RECORD, contentTypeStrategy, readWriteStrategy, recordPlaybackConfiguration);

Date date = new Date();
String text = "extern";
TestClass result = testClass.simpleLevel2Method(3, text, date);

Assert.assertEquals(text, result.getText());

String value = "post_extern";
ReplacementValue replacementValue = ReplacementValueFactory.createReplacementGivenValue(value);
ReplacementConfiguration replacementConfiguration = new ReplacementConfiguration("text", replacementValue);
recordPlaybackConfiguration.addReplacementConfiguration("simpleLevel2Method", replacementConfiguration );
testClass = (TestClass) RecordPlaybackManager.newInstance(TestClass.class, RecordPlaybackMode.PB_OFFLINE, contentTypeStrategy, readWriteStrategy, recordPlaybackConfiguration);

Date date2 = new Date();
result = testClass.simpleLevel2Method(3, text, date2);

Assert.assertEquals(value, result.getText());
```
I want to record/playback the method call `simpleLevel2Method` in `TestClass`.
First I create a `ContentTypeStrategy` and a `ReadWriteStrategy` instance. Then I need a `RecordPlaybackConfiguration` where I define which method arguments indices (here 0 and 1) are used to create a primary key for the recorded value for later retrieval. I create a dynamic proxy instance of my `TestClass` in RECORD Mode. Then I call the method to record the result value.
Afterwards I create a `ReplacementValue`, because I want to change the `text` attribute in my `TestClass` on playback. Then I create a `ReplacementConfiguration` with an attribute path to the `text` attribute and the replacement value and add it to the `RecordPlaybackConfiguration` for `simpleLevel2Method`. I create a dynamic proxy instance of my `TestClass` in PB_OFFLINE Mode. After calling the `simpleLevel2Method` I get the previous recorded value of the `TestClass` except the `text` attribute which returns the value I set with the `ReplacementConfiguration`.
